So

- there is en extra line
- the `*` is always one, don&#39;t need a loop
- the `i` should use `row*2` as bound

&lt;!-- --&gt;

```java
for (row = 0; row &lt; n - 1; row++) {
    for (j = row; j &lt; n - 1; j++) {
        System.out.print(&quot;b&quot;);
    }
    // always
    System.out.print(&quot;*&quot;);
    for (i = 1; i &lt; row * 2; i++) {
        System.out.print(&quot;i&quot;);
    }
    if (row != 0) { // except first line
        System.out.print(&quot;*&quot;);
    }
    for (k = row; k &lt; n - 1; k++) {
        System.out.print(&quot;b&quot;);
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```
-----

Using `String.repeat`

```java
for (row = 0; row &lt; n - 1; row++) {
    String b = &quot;b&quot;.repeat(n - 1 - row);
    String i = &quot;i&quot;.repeat(Math.max(0, row * 2 - 1));
    System.out.println(b + &quot;*&quot; + i + (row != 0 ? &quot;*&quot; : &quot;&quot;) + b);
}
```

