## StringTokenizer is legacy

The `StringTokenizer` is legacy and only included with Java for backward compatibility. It‘s recommended to use `String.split()` for separating a string into tokens.

Full example:

		Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println(&quot;Enter string:&quot;);
		String text = s.nextLine();
		String[] tokens = text.split(&quot; &quot;);
